<chapter xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="ma311-syllabus">
	<title>Syllabus</title>

	<introduction>
		<p>
			Carefully review every item of this syllabus. By taking this course, you are agreeing to the policies laid out in this document. Let me know if you have any questions.  
		</p>
	</introduction>

	<section label="ma311-course-info">
		<title>Course Information</title>
		
		<p>
			<dl width="narrow">
				<li><title>Course Description</title>
					<p>
						Ordinary differential equations (ODEs); Applications; Laplace transforms; Systems of ODEs.
					</p>
				</li>
				<li><title>Meetings</title><p>Room: MH 413 on MWF 1100 - 1150</p></li>
				<li><title>Prerequisite</title><p>Grade of C or better in MA 124</p></li>
				<li><title>Department Head</title><p>COL Troy Siemers</p></li>
				<li><title>Topics (tentative)</title>
					<p>
						The following is a tentative list of topics to be covered. 
						Specific lesson plans and weekly schedules will be provided in class, onn Canvas, or on the course website.
						<ul>
							<li>First-Order Differential Equations</li>
							<li>Linear Constant Coefficient Differential Equations</li>
							<li>Laplace Transforms</li>
							<li>Systems of Differential Equations</li>
							<li>Numerical Methods for Differential Equations</li>
							<li>Qualitative Analysis of Differential Equations</li>
						</ul>
					</p>
				</li>
				<li><title>Final Grade</title>
					<p>
						Your final grade is determined by a combination of the following items:
						<ul>
							<li>Number of Core Topic Passes (# of Ps)</li>
							<li>Number of Secondary Topic Passes (# of Ps)</li>
							<li>Overall Homework Score (%)</li>
							<li>Final Exam Score (%)</li>
						</ul>
						The table below shows that the letter grade you will receive will come from the first row where <term>EVERY</term> requirement is met.
					</p>
				
